<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak PM Leaves for Washington </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif left here tonight for Washington to meet U.S. President
Bill Clinton for discussions on the current situation in Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan, the
meeting is the result of the recent contacts between the two
leaders on the deteriorating situation and the need for a
settlement of the Kashmir dispute which holds the key to durable
peace and security in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister is accompanied by Foreign Minister Sartaj
Aziz and Foreign Secretary Shamshad Ahmad.
</P>
<P>
The report, however, did not mention the duration and the
agenda of Sharif's Washington tour.
</P>
<P>
Sharif paid his last visit to the United States in December
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
