<HEADLINE> Kouchner Regards Security of All Kosovars as Priority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Civil Administrator in
Kosovo Bernard Kouchner said on Saturday that the priority of the
U.N. administration in Kosovo will be to guarantee the security of
all Kosovars.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the French daily Le Monde, Kouchner said
that the U.N. will seek a reconciliation between the Albanian and
Serb communities, besides guaranteeing the security of both.
</P>
<P>
"The mandate of the U.N. is to replace hatred and war with
peace, despite historical heaviness," he said.
</P>
<P>
Appointed by U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan as the head of the
U.N. civil mission in Kosovo, the French state secretary of health
will quit his post in Paris and leave for New York next week, before
going to Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Kouchner called on the international community to contribute
financially to the reconstruction of Kosovo, and to provide help
to whoever in Yugoslavia in need, no matter Albanians or Serbs.
</P>
<P>
He rejected the demand by the Albanian guerrilla group the Kosovo
Liberation Army (KLA) that it be the main component of a future
civil police force in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
"We should not recruit the members of KLA. We should recruit
policemen according to objective criteria, including education
qualification and sense of duty," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
