<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SADC Members Urged to Increase Regional Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Botswana President Festus
Mogae has called for increased trade between Botswana and Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Speaking Saturday in Zambia's Copperbelt Province, when he
opened this year's Zambia International Trade Fair, Mogae said
trade which has been growing steadily between Botswana and Zambia
over the past years should be boosted by an aggressive marketing
of products between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He told audience which included Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba that the plan by the government of Zambia and Botswana to
build a bridge across the Zambezi River at Kazungula to link the
two countries is one way of increasing trade and traffic movement
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Mogae said the development of a reliable transport and
communications infrastructure is critical to the promotion of
trade and investment and regional integration especially in the
Southern African Development Community (SADC) region.
</P>
<P>
He told the fair participants that the envisaged SADC free
trade area will establish a large regional market with the view to
generating opportunities for private business to realize economies
of scale, improved productivity and to become competitive in world
markets.
</P>
<P>
Mogae further said vibrant regional market will become a lunch
for industries in the SADC region to penetrate the would market.
</P>
<P>
He therefore called on countries in the SADC region to
implement tight monetary and prudent fiscal policies to achieve
high growth rates and sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
Mogae said measures being taken in the region like the
successful privatization program implemented by the Zambian
government will go a long way toward facilitating private sector
growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
