<HEADLINE> Mideast Peace Depends on Barak's Policies: Syrian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Radio stressed Saturday
that revival of the Middle East peace march depends on the path
and policies Israeli Prime Minister-elect Ehud Barak is to take.
</P>
<P>
Official Damascus Radio said in its political commentary that
the practical policies of the Israeli in-coming government would
reflect whether Barak is sincere to revive the long-deadlocked
peace process.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that Syria has been adhering to the policy
of peace since Madrid Conference in 1991 and determined to restore
its land, national rights as well as regional security and
stability peacefully in the benefit of all peoples.
</P>
<P>
The radio said Syria is for the just and comprehensive peace in
accordance with the principle set in Madrid Conference and the
U.N. Security Council resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Syria is insisting that its peace talks with Israel on all
tracks restart from where they were left and lead to a complete
Israeli withdrawal from the Golan Heights, south Lebanon and other
occupied Arab territories without violating the national
sovereignty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
