<HEADLINE> German Soldier And Albanians Injured in Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 3 (Xinhua) -- One German soldier of the KFOR and
three Albanian civilians were injured Saturday in an explosion
near the Kosovar city of Prizren, the Press and Information Office
of the German Defense Ministry said in Bonn.
</P>
<P>
A farmer had notified the German KFOR force after finding
ammunition three kilometer west of Prizren.
</P>
<P>
A soldier accompanied the farmer to the site. The farmer picked
up the ammunition which exploded before the soldier was able to
intervene, the ministry said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
