<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sudan, Jordan to Promote Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian King Abdullah Bin
Hussein concluded his five-hour visit to Sudan Saturday after
meeting Sudanese President Omar Bashir on promoting bilateral
economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A joint statement released after the meeting said the two
leaders are keen on revitalizing all pacts signed between the two
governments.
</P>
<P>
They agreed on the need to better the bilateral co-operation
through the joint Sudanese-Jordanian higher commission, whose next
meeting is to be held in Amman, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders discussed ways to revive the Arab solidarity
and achieve just and comprehensive peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
The talks also covered the domains of environmental protection,
expertise exchange and cooperation in animal husbandry, irrigation
and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah has visited Yemen before came to Sudan and he will
also visit Morocco and Mauaritania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
