<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambican President Stresses Quality of African </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano Saturday called on African companies to improve quality
of their goods so that they are in a better position to explore
the market.
</P>
<P>
Opening an international trade fair in the Tanzanian capital
Dar es Salaam, Chissano said high quality products met demands of
consumers and are therefore easily marketable.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that African countries could enter
the 21st century with products of international standards that
could sell anywhere in the world, which will in turn enhance their
economic strength.
</P>
<P>
Chissano, who arrived in Tanzania Friday for a three-day visit,
said trade fairs are important venues for sharing of experience,
and building up and strengthening relationships among countries.
</P>
<P>
Developing countries need to tap their vast potential, the
president said.
</P>
<P>
Chissano commended the Tanzanian first lady, Anna Mkapa, for
her efforts to motivate so many women to participate the fair.
</P>
<P>
Over 370 women exhibitors have participated in the trade fair
with the assistance from the first lady who is a leader of the
Equal Opportunity for All Trust Fund, a women and children
non-governmental organization.
</P>
<P>
The function was also attended by Tanzanian President Benjamin
Mkapa, senior government officials and foreign envoys.
</P>
<P>
The trade fair, the 23rd of its kind, will last until July 10.
It has attracted businessmen from China, France, India, Oman,
South Africa, Uganda, Britain, Iran, Rwanda, Syria and other
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
