<HEADLINE> Spanish World Champion not Expects Easy Rivals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA, Spain, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Despite being the hosts, the
Spanish gymnasts are not expecting they will face easy rivals at
the gymnastic competitions of the 20th University Games.
</P>
<P>
Jesus Carballo, the 1996 world champion of horizontal bar in
Puerto Rico, said that "all the teams bring people of a lot of
level, since all the countries consider this competition important.
"
</P>
<P>
"In this sense, they are not easy rivals," he said while the
men's team competitions started Sunday evening.
</P>
<P>
Citing the tradition of some countries in the Universiade,
Carballo said he believes the level of the United States and
Canada will be high, while other teams like Russia and China also
field in very competitive squads.
</P>
<P>
"As for others, they also contribute with very competitive
teams and can always give some surprises, although they are
without top-notched gymnasts," he said.
</P>
<P>
"And we will give our best in one of the momentous competitions
of 1999," the Spanish gymnast added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
