<HEADLINE> American Players Flexible for All Styles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA, Spain, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The American basketball
players are not in any mood to care about the others as they are
confident of adapting to all styles in the Palma Universiade.
</P>
<P>
"It's a very flexible group, able to carry out very different
game conception," said US basketball team trainer Oliver Purnell.
</P>
<P>
"We have tall men, which allows us to carry out any interior
game of great effectiveness," he said. "and we also have fast men,
that facilitates us the counterback."
</P>
<P>
Purnell, who has 21 years to his credit as coach in the campus
level, declined to cite out any purticular player as "there are 10
players, all of them very good. Joining the abilities of all them,
the result is an excellent team."
</P>
<P>
As the most honored team in different Universiades, the
American players do not demonstrate any concern for their rivals.
</P>
<P>
"I don't know what level the other groups have," Purnell said,"
but I have references of Canada, Spain and Mexico because some
Mexican players play in the United States."
</P>
<P>
However, the American trainer still relunctant to promise an
easy victory as "we also trust that some teams will emerge and
perhaps give the surprise."
</P>
<P>
Citing the differences of the sports between American and
Europe, Purnell said that "it is true that the concept of
university sports is different, but every time there are better
university teams in Europe." 
</P>
</TEXT>
