<HEADLINE> Kirsipuu Claims Lottery of Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Estonian Jann Kirsipuu took the 208km
first stage of the Tour de France in Challans on Sunday in a
sprint finish, but American Lance Armstrong retained the overall
leader's yellow jersey.
</P>
<P>
Kirsipuu, 29, beat home Belgian Tom Steels with German Erik
Zabel in third while Australian Stuart O'Grady was fourth, reports
said reaching here.
</P>
<P>
"I've laid to rest those criticisms that I wasn't a top rider
because I couldn't win a stage on this Tour even though I have won
on all the other major races," Kirsipuu was quoted as saying.
