<HEADLINE> Unseeded Yigang Wins Men's Title at Malaysian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded Luo Yigang of China
beat Malaysian Wong Choon Han 17-16, 17-15 to win the men's
singles final at the Malaysian Open badminton tournament on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The women's title went to second seed Dai Yun of China who beat
joint third seed and compatriot Gong Ruina 11-6, 11-3.
</P>
<P>
Yigang was matched point-for-point in both sets until the end.
It was revenge for Yigang, as Commonwealth Games champion Wong had
beaten him in the Konica Cup in Singapore last year.
</P>
<P>
"I gave it my best shot, but it was not enough," Wong said. "It
was just unfortunate I was beaten so narrowly."
</P>
<P>
Yigang had paved the way for victory with a defeat of
compatriot and world champion Sun Jun in the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Dai's victory over Gong took just 27 minutes and was her first
Malaysian Open title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
