<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pace-setting Shenhua Slaps Wanda at China League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Reigning league champions Dalian
Wanda kept reeling in the first division of Chinese soccer league
as they were humiliated by leaders Shanghai Shenhua 1-3 at home
court on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Wanda, who snatched their first win of the season with a 3-1
victory over Guangzhou Songri on June 24, has slumped back to the
familiar losing form as they fell to their 10th unwinning match in
a 1-2 loss to Beijing Guo'an last round.
</P>
<P>
Wan Tao, the most prolific scorer in the past five seasons,
finally found the net for the first time in the sixth season but
could not yet salvage his team from the second home-court loss
since the league was inniated six years ago.
</P>
<P>
Wanda maintained its home perfect record until this season's
opening match when they fell 0-1 to Liaoning Fushun.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai went ahead in the 15th minute before Wang Tao
converted a penalty to level the scoring on 29 mintues.
</P>
<P>
Shenhua pulled away in the 61st minute and completed the
scoring through substitute Xie Hui in injury time.
</P>
<P>
Newly-appointed coach Li Yingfa said after the match that the
lack of depth has brought the high-flying Wanda, four-time winners
of in the past five years, to land.
</P>
<P>
"The lack of depth is highlighted in the defence which is too
young to stand the test of the serie A."
</P>
<P>
But the coach remained optimistic about the prospect of Wanda
who are struggling on the brink of demotion.
</P>
<P>
"What Wanda lost is just a match against Shenhua, not the whole
season. We should keep up our confidence to do well in the next
half season."
</P>
<P>
"Now we are placed at the bottom, we need more wins. Only when
we fought our way out of the relegation zone could we set our
sight on further aims."
</P>
<P>
The 1995 league champions Shanghai Shenhua, who became the
newest pace-setters for the first time this season by beating
Guangzhou Songri 2-1 on home turf last round, kept their lead with
a 6-7-0 unbeaten record.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Quanxin was held to a scoreless tie by Shenzhen Ping'an
and elbowed out the top three by Luneng Taishan who scored an away
win over the lowly Wuhang Heart K 1-0.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing Longxin remained on the heels of the Shenhua with a
two-point margin as the visiting outfit slammed Shengyang Haishi 2-
1 for 23 points.
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere Jilin Aodong lost to Qingdao Hainiu 1-2 at home and
Liaoning Fushun was held to a 1-1 tie by visiting Beijing Guo'an.
Guangzhou Songri collected a home 2-0 victory over Tianjin Taida.
</P>
</TEXT>
