<HEADLINE> Shanghai Establishes Chemical Industry Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- China's leading industrial and
commercial city of Shanghai has started to build a chemical
industry park open to both domestic and overseas investors, as
part of the city's efforts to foster new and high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Chemical Industry Park, located in Jinshan
District in the southern part of the city, covers an area of 22 sq
km.
</P>
<P>
The park, scheduled for completion by 2016, will concentrate on
the manufacture of various high-tech petrochemical products that
are marketable, capable of saving resources and are environmental
friendly.
</P>
<P>
So far, about a dozen multinationals, including Germany's BASF
and Japan's NPU, have already signed agreements to set up
subsidiaries in the park.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai first decided to give priority to new and high-tech
industries in 1995. By the end of last year, such industries
reported nearly 100 billion yuan (12 billion US dollars) in output
value, accounting for 16.5 percent of the city's overall
industrial output the same year.
</P>
<P>
The city has targeted its high-tech industry output value at
120 billion yuan this year, up 25 percent from last year. The
growth is double the rate for this year's expected industrial
growth.  
</P>
</TEXT>
