<HEADLINE> NPC Vice Chairman Meets Panchen Lama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIGATSE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Pagbalha Geleg Namgyai, a vice
chairman of the National People's Congress Standing Committee,
visited today the 11th Panchen Erdini Qoigyijabu at the latter's
residence in Shigatse, the Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The NPC vice chairman, who is an ethnic Tibetan himself, said
he was very glad to learn that the Panchen Lama is in good health
and making progress in studying Buddhism.
</P>
<P>
He also thanked the Zhaxi Lhumbo Lamasery's Buddhist masters
for their hard work in fostering the Panchen Lama.
</P>
<P>
The Panchen Lama express his cordial thanks to the NPC vice
chairman for his visit, saying, "Since I was reincarnated three
years ago, I have worked hard to study Buddhism and other
knowledge and have made quite big strides."
</P>
<P>
The Panchen Lama expressed his satisfaction over his current
Buddhist tours in Lhasa and Shigatse.
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, the Panchen Lama also met with the 17th Garmaba O'
kying Chilai, the 15-year old head of the white sect of the
Tibetan Buddhism who was enthroned in 1992 to become the first
Tibetan living Buddha approved by the Chinese central government
since 1949.
</P>
<P>
The Garmaba arrived here from Lahsa to visit the Panchen Lama.
The two living Buddhas exchanged greetings and souvenirs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
