<HEADLINE> Rossi Wins British 250cc Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Valentino Rossi beat fellow Italian
Loris Capirossi to take the British 250cc motorcycling grand prix
in Donington Park, England, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It was his fourth victory of the season and brought him to
within seven points of championship leader Tohru Ukawa of Japan
who was fourth, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Capirossi, 250cc champion and last year's winner in Donington
Park, took the lead on the 13th lap of a race interrupted by rain
but Rossi regained the lead on his Aprilia with four laps to go.
He won in 42 minutes 54.311 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Shinya Nakano of Japan, riding a Yamaha, was third.
</P>
<P>
Ukawa leads at the midway point of the championship with 147
points. Rossi is second with 140 and Nakano has 112. Capirossi is
fourth on 102. 
</P>
</TEXT>
