<HEADLINE> Japan Humiliates Philippines at Asian Olympic qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Japan thrashed the Philippines 11-0
here on Sunday to complete a perfect eight straight wins at the
second leg of the Asian Olympic qualifying tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese, who scored a total of 52 goals and conceded only
one goal in eight games, joined South Korea, China, Qatar, Kuwait,
Bahrain and Kazakhstan in the final qualifying round slated from
October 1 to November 15.
</P>
<P>
Japan, who shut out the Philippines 13-0 in the first leg, went
ahead five minutes into time with Tomoyuki Hirase hitting home the
first of his hat-trick.
</P>
<P>
Shunsuke Nakamura added two more, while Shinji Ono, Daisuke
Ichikawa, Masashi Motoyama, Tomokazu Myojin and Kazuyuki Toda were
also on target in the end.
</P>
<P>
They suffered their only setback when Ono and Yasuhito Endo
were sidelined for injuries in the 34th and 27th minutes
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong finished second with 4-1-3 for 13 points. Malaysia,
who defeated Nepal 3-2 earlier in the day, stood a 3-2-3 record
for 11 points, beating Nepal into four with a 2-2-4 for eight and
the Philippines bottom with a 0-1-7 for one. 
</P>
</TEXT>
