<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-04 13:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Blasts Western Countries for Interference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Majlis (parliament) Speaker
Ali Akbar Nateq Nouri Sunday castigated the stance adopted by
western countries towards the arrest of 13 Iranian Jews on
espionage charges.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Majlis opening session, Nouri termed the stance
of the western countries as "a blatant interference and meddling"
in Iran's internal affairs, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian speaker made the remarks in a response to the
recent stance taken by some American congressmen and 143 French
lawmakers in support of the arrested Iranian Jews.
</P>
<P>
He said that the same people and governments, which remained
indifference to the downing of Iranian passenger plane by the
U.S. warship in 1988, have now made a big fuss in the world over
the arrest of 13 Iranian Jews under the pretext of defense for
human rights.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. warship Vincennes shot down the Iranian airbus plane
with two missiles on July 3, 1988, killing all the 290 passengers
and crew aboard. Iran Saturday demanded an official apology from
the U.S. over the issue.
</P>
<P>
Nouri said that no one is being prosecuted in Iran for
advocating certain belief or religion, and today different
minorities are living together with their Muslim brothers and
sisters and are entitled to all citizenship rights.
</P>
<P>
There are people who are arrested in Iran on charges of
smuggling drugs, robbery or links with aliens and their cases are
investigated, he said. The arrest of the 13 Jews is also in the
same line and their charges will be also investigated, he added.
</P>
<P>
Nouri stressed that Iran's foreign policy is based on mutual
respect, observance of the rights of the people and preservation
of national interests.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the European statesmen who are
interested in having relations with the Islamic Republic of Iran
respect the mentioned principles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
