<HEADLINE> U.S. General Electric Company Opens Office in Dalian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. General Electric Co. (GE)
has opened a business office in Dalian, a coastal city in
northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
"The move shows GE's wish and determination to expand its
market in Dalian and the northeastern part of China," said Goran
Malm, the company's vice-president, explaining that Dalian, a city
located at the junction point of China, Russia, Japan and the
Republic of Korea, has unique advantages both in culture and
commerce.
</P>
<P>
GE has opened up more than 20 offices in China, employing more
than 6,000 Chinese people and investing more than one billion U.S.
dollars in the country, a source said.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that GE's business in China has just started and we
are willing to do more," Malm said.
</P>
<P>
"GE's business will cover three aspects -- to provide more
products and services in China, to purchase more products from
China and to seek business partners," Malm added.  
</P>
