<HEADLINE> Iranian Vice President Starts Latin American Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Iranian First Vice President Hassan
Habibi Sunday started Latin American three-nation tour for talks
with leaders of these countries on the latest international
developments and ways of strengthening bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Habibi Sunday left for his first leg, Colombian capital
Bogota. During his one-week trip, he will also visit Venezuela and
Cuba, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Terming cooperation between Iran and Venezuela, especially
within the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC)
as good, he said that the future issues of the OPEC would top the
agenda of his talks with Venezuelan officials.
</P>
<P>
Habibi also said that expansion of mutual scientific and
cultural relations would be one of other pivotal issues of his
talks in the Latin American tour.
</P>
<P>
Talks between Iranian delegation and officials of these
countries would be effective in expanding mutual ties and
cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Iranian Commerce Minister Mohammad Shariatmadari,
who is accompanying Habibi in the tour, said that Iran has made a
comprehensive plan to promote economic relations with Latin
American states.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the potential and existing capabilities for
cooperation with these countries, he said that Iran would discuss
signing of agreements on economic cooperation with the three
countries during his tour. 
</P>
