<HEADLINE>   Malaysia Beats Nepal 3-2 at Asian Olympic Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia ended up third in the Asian
group six qualifying tournament after a second leg 3-2 victory
over Nepal here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In the first leg of the qualifier for the Sydney Olympics held
in Hong Kong two weeks ago, Nepalese fans invaded the pitch in the
dying seconds. And the football's world governing body considered
the game a 1-1 tie shortly before the second leg started.
</P>
<P>
Akmal Rizal Rakhili opened the scoring for Malaysia with a
right foot shot in the 23rd minute before Rajan Raymajhi equalized
it six minutes later.
</P>
<P>
But Nepalese fans in the stadium were silenced early in the
second half when Chow Chee Weng made it 2-1 in the 53rd minute and
Rakhili added another two minutes later.
</P>
<P>
It was too late when Deepak Lama pulled one back for Nepal in
the 87th minute.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia finished with three wins, two draws and three defeats
for 11 points to place third. Nepal was fourth on eight points.
</P>
<P>
Japan had already secured top place to join South Korea, China,
Qatar, Kuwait, Bahrain and Kazakhstan for the last Asian
qualifying round for the Olympic competition in the 2000.
</P>
<P>
A draw for the final Asian round from October 1 to November 15
will be held in Los Angeles on July 8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
