others wounded in a shoot-out between the country's two main rival
guerrilla groups in eastern Lebanon's Bekaa valley.
</P>
<P>
The Voice of the People radio Sunday quoted security sources as
saying that Ali Suleiman Horshi, 30, member of the Iranian-backed
Hezbollah, or Party of God, died Sunday after he sustained a
serious injury in a gun battle with members of the Shiite Muslim
Amal movement at Sohmor in Bekaa.
</P>
<P>
The clash erupted from a quarrel and developed into an armed
conflict which led to the intervention of government troops.
</P>
