searching for the rest involved in the clash.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah and Amal have long been vying for the leadership of
the country's largest single Shiite Muslim community which
accounts for one third of the country's 3.5 million population.
</P>
<P>
The two groups are also fighting to dislodge Israeli occupation
forces out of south Lebanon where it set up a self-declared
security zone in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north
from Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border attacks. 
