<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 4 (Xinhua) -- China's Nanhai Dragon Boat Team
claimed the title of the Men's International Cup Championship in
the Hong Kong Dragon Boat Festival -- International Races 1999
Sunday afternoon at Shatin.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Tsing Yi Yuen Yuen Dragon Boat Team and Philippine
Canoe Federation/Drago Philippines Mixed Team ranked the 2nd and
the 3rd in the premier race of the two-day event.
</P>
<P>
Most members of the Nanhai team are farmers in Southern China
and this is the fifth time for them to compete in the Hong Kong
races. They finished the 640-meter race in 2 minutes and 46.69
seconds.
</P>
<P>
The Tsing Yi team achieved the best result among some 90 local
crews by finishing the race in 2 minutes and 51.87 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines outfit, consisting mainly of national team
members, ended up the race in 2 minutes and 58.37 seconds. It was
set up in 1996 with a view of promoting canoeing and kayaking in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Though the Philippine failed to lift the cup, they did get
three championships in the races.
</P>
<P>
The RP Navy--Marine Corps Rowing Team won the Men's
International Plate Championship; the Navy--Dragon Paddlers took
the Mixed International Championship while the Dragon Peddlers
ranked the 1st in the Hong Kong Provisional Regional Council Women
's International Championship.
</P>
<P>
The local team of the Hung Hing Yui Kee Co. Ltd. won the Men's
International Bowl Championship.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the international championships, there were also
races featuring local professionals, disciplinary forces
servicemen and students.
</P>
<P>
A total of 27 teams from 7 countries and regions around the
world and 90 local teams competed the races. Teams from China's
mainland, Canada, Japan, Italy, Macao, the Philippines and the
United States took part in the event organized by the Hong Kong
Tourism Association (HKTA) in conjunction with the Provisional
Regional Council. 
