<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Airport Receives 29,298,888th Passenger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong International
Airport received the 29,298,888th passenger Sunday afternoon since
it began operation one year ago.
</P>
<P>
Shuichi Isaka, a businessman from Tokyo, was lucky to become
the landmark guest in his Hong Kong tour with his wife. He was
greeted by Victor Fung, chairman of the Hong Kong Airport
Authority, on arrival.
</P>
<P>
To mark the first anniversary of the new airport, an exhibition
with the name of "Hong Kong International Airport -- Ready for the
Millennium" opened Sunday at the airport.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, Fung said the Hong Kong
International Airport serves as an important channel to link Asia
and the world, and airliners leading to some 110 cities worldwide
fly from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He noted the passenger and cargo transport volume handled by
the airport increased by 4 percent and 6 percent respectively in
May 1999, compared to the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong new airport at Chek Lap Kok started commercial
operation on July 6, 1998, since the old Kai Tak Airport could not
meet the demands of increasing passenger and cargo transportation.
</P>
<P>
When the Northwest Concourse and the second runway go into full
operation, the airport is expected to handle 45 million passengers
and 3 million tons of cargo each year, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
