<HEADLINE> Boat Accident Kills 3 in Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Three people drowned and over 20
more are still missing who feared dead when a passenger boat
capsized after colliding with a steel bridge on Saturday in
Shehong County of southwest China's Sichuan province.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses of the accident said the engine boat sailed off the
dock at about 11:20 am and the steering device seemed to break
down afterwards. The boat was seen drifting down the Fujiang River
about 500 meters before it ran into a steel bridge and capsized.
The over 40 passengers aboard fell into the river, with 12 of them
rescued and all the others swept away.
</P>
<P>
The sinking site, Jinhua Township of Shehong County, is about
150 kilometers east of the provincial capital Chengdu.
</P>
<P>
Rescure workers organized by the local government recovered
three bodies so far and the salvage work is still under way.
</P>
</TEXT>
