<HEADLINE> Chinese Striker Yang Chen Transferred to Frankfurt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese striker Yang Chen, who had
played for the German club of Frankfurt on loan for the past
season, has been transferred to the club, China's first division
club Beijing Guo'An confirmed here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-based Chinese club transferred the 25-year-old on a
sum of 3.75 million yuan RMB (0.85 million German marks),
according to the contract signed here last Friday.
</P>
<P>
A former Guo'An striker, Yang had been selected into China's
national team and Olympic side. Last season, he became the first
ever Chinese to play in any first division German club, on loan
for Frankfurt. Yang's team-high eight goals during the season
helped the German club stay in the top division.
</P>
<P>
Terms for Yang's transfer were discussed and settled at talks
with Frankfurt's vice-chairman Gaetano Patella during his earlier
visits to Beijing.
</P>
<P>
At its height in domestic soccer league, Beijing Guo'An
finished runners-up in 1995, the second season of China's
professional league. It is now ranked 11th among the 14 first-
division teams in this season's league competitions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
