<HEADLINE> Chile Keeps Quarterfinals Hopes Alive after Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Chile overcame a sluggish
start to beat Venezuela 3-0 in Ciudad del Este, Paraguay, on
Saturday and remain in contention for a quarterfinal berth in Copa
America.
</P>
<P>
Ivan Zamorano, Jose Luis Sierra, and Edson Torterolo each
scored a goal in a match marred by red card and rain.
</P>
<P>
Recovering from a stunning 7-0 loss to Brazil, Venezuela had to
play most of the Saturday game with 10 players, after Rolando
Alvarez was sent off in the 17th minute for fouling Chilean
striker Marcelo Salas.
</P>
<P>
With a man advantage and Venezuela's defense exposing gaping
holes, the Chileans launched wave upon wave of attacks, only
missing several easy chances through Zamorano and Salas.
</P>
<P>
Zamorano penetrated deep into Venezuela's defense, and was
managing to maneuver around goalkeeper Renny Vega to make a lethal
shot. But the ball was pushed away by a Venezuela defender before
it crossed the goal line.
</P>
<P>
Chile's numerical advantage was gone minutes near the end of
the first half when Jorge Vargas received a red card. Chile's
Salas was sent off in the second half and will not play in the
next game against Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Brazil leads Group B with six points. Chile and Mexico are
tied for the second place with three points each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
