<HEADLINE> U.S. Shooter Wins Women's Trap at Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Cindy Gentry of the United States
won the women's trap title in the World Shooting Championships in
Lempaala on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Gentry, 44, sixth last year, hit 94 of 100 targets. Finnish
Satu Pusila, the 1998 winner, was second with 93, followed by
French Delphine Racinet at 92.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Veryanik Avetisyan won the skeet event by hitting 96
of the 100. Italy's Christina Vitali was ranked second at 94, and
Russian Svetlana Demina had to settle for the bronze medal with 92.
</P>
</TEXT>
