<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "The Four Teams are On the Same Level", Chinese Coac h </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BOSTON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese coach Ma Yuanan said the four
teams in the semifinals of the 3rd women's World Cup soccer tournament
are on the same level.
</P>
<P>
China, Norway, the United States and Brazil are the four teams
in the semifinals which slated for July 4 at San Francisco and
Boston respectively.
</P>
<P>
"The four teams deserve to be the semifinals. It's hard to say
which one are better than the other one. Each of the four teams have
a chance of entering the finals."
</P>
<P>
China will play defending champions Norway at Boston while hosts
the United States will take on Brazil at San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
Ma Yuanan said the Chinese team were in good form:"We have no
serious injury problems. My players are in high spirit. They are
now ready for the match against Norway."
</P>
<P>
Ma praised the Norway team, saying the defending champions are
quite strong physically and very quick in attacking. But he said
his team would not be frightened.
</P>
<P>
"Anything can happen in the semifinals since the four teams are
on the same level. The result of the match between Norway and China
will be decided by the performances of the players. If we play
better, then we will win the match." said Ma Yuanan.
</P>
<P>
"Of course, we want to enter the final, it's a dream for all of
our players, especially for those who will retire after the World
Cup or after the Olympic Games. We will try our best to fulfill our
dream." said Ma Yuanan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
