<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0510 GMT, July 4 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM -- Jordanian King Abdullah Bin Hussein concluded his
five-hour visit to Sudan Saturday after meeting Sudanese President
Omar Bashir on promoting bilateral economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A joint statement released after the meeting said the two
leaders are keen on revitalizing all pacts signed between the two
governments. (Sudan-Jordan-Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- Leaders of the Balkan countries are concerned over
the West's initial promises of substantial aid for the whole of
South-Eastern Europe since they believed that the aid of
reconstruction appeared to have been watered down.
</P>
<P>
The West has promised a huge new "Marshall Plan" of the aid for
Balkan reconstruction, but the sums are steadily shrinking while
the focus was being narrowed to Kosovo itself, according to a
twice-weekly European Report issued on Saturday. (Balkan Leaders-
Reconstruction-Worries)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA -- Colombia's foreign reserves dropped to 8.
364 billion U.S. dollars on June 25 because of rising speculation
in the country, the Bank of the Republic reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The reserves stood at 8.712 billion dollars at the end of May,
but fell by 347.1 million dollars after the central bank
intervened the market with 274.87 million dollars on May 24-25 to
maintain the currency exchange rate. (Colombia-Foreign Reserves)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
QUITO -- The Ecuadorian government is planning to turn the
country into a "wonderland" for foreign visitors under a regional
tourism plan, Tourism Minister Rocio Vasque said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, Ecuador will cooperate with other
countries in the region to establish a regional tourism
integration program. (Ecuador-Tourism)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA -- Colombia should develop alternate sources
of energy, experts of the Mining and Energy Ministry said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Colombia has a high potential for the development of alternate
sources of energy, but the high cost of research and development
has prevented their mass production, said Josue Zapata and Luis
Carlos Romero, experts from the ministry. (Colombia-Alternate
Energy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Brazil is working on a sustainable development
program for forestry resources, the Environment Ministry said
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The program -- National Forestry Program (Pronaflor) --
foresees the planting of six million hectares of forests with an
annual output of 150 million cubic meters of lumber and 1.5
million job opportunities. (Brazil-Forest Conservation) 
</P>
</TEXT>
