<HEADLINE> 12 Killed, 50 Injured in Road Accident in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 4 (Xinhua) - At least 12 people, including two
children and five women, were killed on the spot and 50 others
were injured when two buses collided head-on in central Bangladesh
on Saturday, The Independent newspaper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A Dhaka-bound mini-bus collided head-on with a Sylhet-bound bus
in Narayanganj District, southeast of here in the afternoon,
police and witnesses said.
</P>
<P>
Nine of the dead were passengers of the bus heading for Sylhet,
208 kilometers northeast of here and three were of the Dhaka-bound
bus.
</P>
<P>
The injured were rushed to hospital, with 23 of them in
critical condition. 
</P>
