<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leadi Times:
</P>
<P>
-- Kandla custom authorities in India's western state of
Gujarat detained a Malta-bound North Korea ship, alleging that it
was on a mission of covertly aiding Pakistan's missile program.
</P>
<P>
The Hindu:
</P>
<P>
-- Pakistan Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif left for Washington
late Saturday night to discuss the Kargil situation with U.S.
President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
The Indian Express:
</P>
<P>
-- A MIG-27 fighter plane of the Indian Air Force crashed
Saturday in southwest India, killing the pilot. 
</P>
