<HEADLINE> Australia and New Zealand to Bid for 2010 World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AUCKLAND, July 4 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand and Australia will
make a joint bid for 2010 World Cup soccer finals, the Sunday News
reported here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It quoted Soccer New Zealand chief executive Bob Patterson who
said he had been in talks with his Australian counterparts. "We're
both capable of hosting the World Cup," he said.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand had the venues capable of holding matches, he said.
</P>
<P>
"I don't know how many games we would get," Patterson said.
</P>
<P>
"But there's no doubt we have the venues available in New
Zealand," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
