<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Singaporean Industrial Park Reports Investment Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Suzhou Industrial Park, a Sino-
Singaporean joint project built in 1994 in Suzhou, a scenic city
in east China's Jiangsu Province, has reported a big increase in
investment from overseas this year.
</P>
<P>
The park approved projects with a combined contractual overseas
capital of 450 million U.S. dollars for the first half of the year,
bringing the total overseas investment to 6.3 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among this year's new overseas investors are six of the world's
top 500 companies: AMP Connector Tool Ltd., Alcatel
Telecommunications Co., Ltd., EKA Chemicals Co., Ltd., LJF Co.,
Ltd., Cutler-Hammer Electric Co., Ltd., and Mitsui Copper Foil Co.,
Ltd..
</P>
<P>
The existing overseas-funded enterprises in the park have shown
a definite propensity to expand their operations. Of the 450
million U.S. dollars, 47 percent is newly added by these
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The Suzhou Industrial Park has led the country's other
development zones in successful expansion, with each overseas-
funded project involving an average of over 30 million U.S.
dollars of investment.
</P>
<P>
So far, some 155 overseas-funded enterprises have been
established in the park, 34 of which are backed by the world's top
companies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
