<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Experts Urge to Develop Alternate Energy in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Colombia should develop
alternate sources of energy, experts of the Mining and Energy
Ministry said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Colombia has a high potential for the development of alternate
sources of energy, but the high cost of research and development
has prevented their mass production, said Josue Zapata and Luis
Carlos Romero, experts from the ministry.
</P>
<P>
They said that Colombia has the resources, the technology, and
the needs to implement this kind of energy sources, but coherence
is needed in the nation policies to define the projects.
</P>
<P>
They explained that alternate energy sources are not
competitive in a big scale, because they are very costly compared
to the one that can be produced with the traditional methods.
</P>
<P>
However, they said this situation will be solved in the medium
term.
</P>
<P>
Wind generated energy was basically used to pump up underground
water, mainly in the northern regions, such as the Guajira, on the
border with Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
Some systems to generate electric energy in a small scale have
been installed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
