<HEADLINE> Messer to Raise China Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The German-based Messer Group, one
of the world's biggest industrial gas producers, plans to expand
its investment in China as part of the company's global strategy,
the China Daily Business Weekly reported today.
</P>
<P>
Messer, which has 17 joint ventures in China, will increase
its investment in China from 190 million U.S. dollars to 300
million by 2000, according to Herbert Rudolf, president of the
Company.
</P>
<P>
Its latest move designed in June is to set up a carbon dioxide
joint venture with the Zhenhai Refinery Co Ltd in Ningbo in east
China's Zhejiang Province, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The venture, involving a total investment of 7.7 million U.S.
dollars, will have an annual output of 50,000 tons of carbon
dioxide used in food freezing and beverage businesses.
</P>
<P>
Messer is also negotiating with the China Petrochemical
Corporation Group for projects involving 100 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Rudolf said China could soon become the first or second
industrial gas market in the world owing to its sustained economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
"When we entered the Chinese market in 1994, we established a
10-year development plan to become the largest supplier of
industrial gas in China and we are progressing very smoothly
towards this goal," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the group's sales volume in China was expected to
reach 500 million yuan (60 million U.S. dollars) this year and
would rise to 2 billion yuan (240.9 million U.S. dollars) in 2003.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
