<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Works on Forestry Development Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Brazil is working on a sustainable
development program for forestry resources, the Environment
Ministry said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The program -- National Forestry Program (Pronaflor) --
foresees the planting of six million hectares of forests with an
annual output of 150 million cubic meters of lumber and 1.5
million job opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The program will be jointly implemented by the Environment
Ministry, the Brazilian Institute of the Environment and Renewable
Natural Resources and the private sector.
</P>
<P>
Brazil has an area of 442 million hectares of forests with a
wood reserve of 65.8 billion cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
The forest area has shrunk over the past years because of the
excessive exploitation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
