<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenedy Ochieng Captures 400m Crown in IAAF Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Kenedy Ochieng won the
400 meters in the IAAF Permit meet here on Saturday, with the
world record-holder Butch Reynolds abscent from the meet.
</P>
<P>
Ochieng clocked 45.44 seconds, in front of Eric Milazar of
Mauritius in 45.60, and 1994 European champion Duaine Ladejo of
England in 45.93. Reynolds was sidelined by an injury.
</P>
<P>
Former world indoor champion John Regis of England struggled in
the 100m and 200m. He finished ninth in the 200m, and failed to
qualify for the 100m in 10.54 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Gabon's Antoine Boussombo won the 100m event in 10.21 and
Hungary's Roland Nemeth claimed the victory in the 200m in 20.50.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 400, three-time indoor world champion Tatiana
Chebykina of Russia came from behind to overtake England's Donna
Frazer in the final meters.
</P>
<P>
Chebykina, who is preparing for the world championships in
August in Seville, Spain, clocked a winning time of 51.67 seconds.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
