<HEADLINE> Torrential Rains Isolate 7,000 People in Western Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- About 7,000 people in 14
communities in the San Francisco Municipality of Nicaragua's
western department of Chinandega Saturday were isolated from the
outside world by torrential rains.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rains over the past two weeks had caused water to
overflow in the region's Agua Buena, El Gallo, El Negro and El
Ubote rivers, said Francisco Espinosa, a Nicaraguan Municipal
Development Institute official.
</P>
<P>
Chinandega department was most affected by the hurricane Mitch
last October and November and a Casita volcano landslide there
buried some 2,500 people in a worst disaster during the same
period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
