<HEADLINE> Berthez Voted France's Most Popular Sports Figure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Soccer goalkeeper Fabien Barthez is
the most popular sports figure in France, edging World Cup-winning
teammate Zinedine Zidane into second place, according to an
opinion poll carried out by a local newspaper, which was to be
published on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Yachtswoman Florence Arthaud came third in the poll of 1,013
French people over 15 years old, according to the poll
commissioned by the Sunday newspaper Journal Du Dimanche.
</P>
<P>
The Monaco goalkeeper obtained 56.7 percent of the votes to
Zidane's 52.5 and 38.6 for Arthaud, the first woman to win the
Route du Rhum trans-Atlantic solo sailing race in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Five footballers are listed in the top 10, with them all
members of the country's 1998 World Cup champions team.
</P>
<P>
The others are new Inter Milan signing Laurent Blanc, captain
Didier Deschamps who has just joined Chelsea, and Arsenal's
Emmanuel Petit. Tottenham Hotspur's David Ginola is 12th.
</P>
<P>
The others in the top 10 are Olympic judo champion David
Douillet, yachtswoman Isabelle Autissier, Formula One motor racer
Jean Alesi and Olympic double sprint champion Marie-Jose Perec.
</P>
