<HEADLINE> Armstrong Wins Tour de France Cycle Race Prologue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- American Lance Armstrong, in his
first Tour de France after recovering from a cancer, made a
fantastic comeback by winning the Tour's 6.8-km prologue in Le Puy
du Fou on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Texan clocked eight minutes and two seconds for the triumph,
which made him the first American since Greg LeMond in 1990 to be
in the race leader's yellow jersey.
</P>
<P>
Armstrong, an unexpected winner in the world road championships
in 1993, beat such time-trial specialists including Switzerland's
Alex Zuelle, who finished second, seven seconds adrift.
</P>
<P>
Among others who followed in the prologue were Spain's time-
trial world champion Abraham Olano, Christophe Moreau of France
and Chris Boardman, the Briton who won the last two Tour prologues.
