</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) has
refused to allow Russia to fly more troops into Kosovo until
details of their mission have been agreed to, U.S officials said
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The alliance expects the Russians this week to continue talks
on the requested revisions, according to an Associated Press
report. (US-Russia-Kosovo) 
</P>
</TEXT>
