<HEADLINE> Colombia's Foreign Reserves Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's foreign
reserves dropped to 8.364 billion U.S. dollars on June 25 because
of rising speculation in the country, the Bank of the Republic
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The reserves stood at 8.712 billion dollars at the end of May,
but fell by 347.1 million dollars after the central bank
intervened the market with 274.87 million dollars on May 24-25 to
maintain the currency exchange rate.
</P>
<P>
The central bank's Board of Directors decided on June 27 to
permit a bigger fluctuation of up to nine percentage points to
prevent spending more reserves. 
</P>
