<HEADLINE> Colombian Rebel Intelligence Chief Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A female chief of
Colombia's largest rebel group -- the Revolutionary Armed Forces
of Colombia (FARC) -- was arrested in the Vanguardia airport of
Villavicencio, capital of Meta department, a Colombian police
official announced Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ruth Lucena Grisales, FARC's eastern block general staff member,
was arrested when boarding a plane bound for Barranco Minas in
Guainia, said Colonel Delfin Cortes Caviedes, Secret Police chief
in Meta.
</P>
<P>
Grisales, 33, handles intelligence operations and coordination
among different guerrilla fronts in the prairies of eastern
Colombia. 
